1
00:00:01,026 --> 00:00:03,026
What do you think you're doing?

2
00:00:18,679 --> 00:00:20,755
(Tarot Reading See your destiny)

3
00:00:32,500 --> 00:00:35,259
You think this is my first time
dealing with people like you?

4
00:00:35,260 --> 00:00:36,070
People like me?

5
00:00:36,071 --> 00:00:37,299
What did I even do?

6
00:00:37,300 --> 00:00:38,290
Just because you're a star,

7
00:00:38,291 --> 00:00:40,714
you think you can do whatever you want?

8
00:00:40,715 --> 00:00:41,999
Isn't it you, though...

9
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:44,457
The one sending those disgusting
letters to my house.

10
00:00:44,458 --> 00:00:46,939
Following me like a shadow
and selling photos like a creep.

11
00:00:46,940 --> 00:00:48,259
I said it wasn't me!

12
00:00:48,260 --> 00:00:50,779
Okay, okay, everyone calm down.

13
00:00:50,780 --> 00:00:54,901
I need to get home for my cat's livestream.

14
00:01:00,965 --> 00:01:03,465
Are you mocking me right now?

15
00:01:03,490 --> 00:01:06,749
At least you're decent looking.

16
00:01:06,750 --> 00:01:08,509
"Handsome", my ass...

17
00:01:08,510 --> 00:01:11,525
You look like a cat's nut sack.

18
00:01:11,526 --> 00:01:13,169
Hey! That's verbal abuse!

19
00:01:13,170 --> 00:01:14,020
That's an insult!

20
00:01:14,021 --> 00:01:15,539
I'm suing him!

21
00:01:15,540 --> 00:01:17,600
Geonwoo!!!

22
00:01:20,594 --> 00:01:21,815
Are... are you okay?

23
00:01:21,816 --> 00:01:23,379
Wh-wh-what happened?!

24
00:01:23,380 --> 00:01:24,799
Call my lawyer.

25
00:01:24,800 --> 00:01:27,361
Uh... I was going to...

26
00:01:27,740 --> 00:01:30,689
You think I don't have a lawyer?

27
00:01:30,690 --> 00:01:32,838
What do you need a lawyer for?

28
00:01:32,839 --> 00:01:34,300
This is exactly when you need one.

29
00:01:34,301 --> 00:01:36,442
I have one too, just you wait.

30
00:01:38,049 --> 00:01:43,070
(That law school kid! Finally useful.
(I'm being framed. Give me your number.)

31
00:01:45,340 --> 00:01:46,339
Pick three cards.

32
00:01:46,340 --> 00:01:47,840
What?

33
00:01:48,374 --> 00:01:49,910
But where are you...

34
00:01:49,911 --> 00:01:51,792
Focus on your question first.

35
00:01:51,793 --> 00:01:54,494
Then pick three from the table.

36
00:01:54,495 --> 00:01:56,495
Oh...

37
00:02:01,188 --> 00:02:05,070
Will Jaeyeon like me?

38
00:02:24,025 --> 00:02:26,013
Pick one more.

39
00:02:33,300 --> 00:02:34,882
Hmm... you'll get one chance.

40
00:02:34,883 --> 00:02:35,883
What?

41
00:02:36,810 --> 00:02:39,900
If you miss that moment,
you'll be friends forever...

42
00:02:44,900 --> 00:02:46,819
(That law school kid! Finally useful.
(I'm being framed. Give me your number.)

43
00:02:46,820 --> 00:02:48,540
(Calling Jaeyeon)

44
00:02:56,210 --> 00:02:57,050
It was 20,000 won, though.
(T/N: He only gave 10,000 won.)

45
00:02:58,430 --> 00:03:01,321
Lawyer! Over here!

46
00:03:01,675 --> 00:03:02,560
Hey, what's going on?

47
00:03:02,561 --> 00:03:05,892
Taewoo, he keeps calling me a creep...

48
00:03:05,893 --> 00:03:07,549
A stalker...!

49
00:03:07,550 --> 00:03:09,919
Jaeyeon?

50
00:03:09,920 --> 00:03:12,149
What's going on here?

51
00:03:12,150 --> 00:03:13,949
You brought him here?

52
00:03:13,950 --> 00:03:16,163
Jaeyeon?

53
00:03:16,490 --> 00:03:18,217
You.

54
00:03:18,218 --> 00:03:19,933
What did you do to my brother?

55
00:03:19,934 --> 00:03:20,979
Bullshit...

56
00:03:20,980 --> 00:03:22,339
What's really going on?

57
00:03:22,340 --> 00:03:23,650
Yeah, what the hell...?

58
00:03:23,651 --> 00:03:25,672
What happened?

59
00:03:27,434 --> 00:03:31,277
I got the CCTV footage.

60
00:03:31,740 --> 00:03:34,239
Should we take a look?

61
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:35,300
Fine, play it.

62
00:03:40,400 --> 00:03:42,275
This guy...

63
00:03:45,460 --> 00:03:48,061
I don't think he's a stalker...

64
00:03:53,760 --> 00:03:55,599
Really?

65
00:03:55,600 --> 00:03:57,120
"Really"?!

66
00:03:58,610 --> 00:03:59,838
Here's your chance.

67
00:03:59,839 --> 00:04:01,474
What...?

68
00:04:01,475 --> 00:04:02,735
An interview.

69
00:04:02,736 --> 00:04:04,536
Forget the apology,
get an interview instead.

70
00:04:06,220 --> 00:04:08,479
I know my brother.

71
00:04:08,726 --> 00:04:10,769
Don't expect a sincere apology from him.

72
00:04:10,770 --> 00:04:11,939
I can apologize for Geonwoo...

73
00:04:11,940 --> 00:04:13,653
No, it's fine.

74
00:04:14,870 --> 00:04:17,179
How about some compensation then?

75
00:04:17,180 --> 00:04:18,819
Is a million won enough?

76
00:04:18,820 --> 00:04:21,250
Better than an apology, right?

77
00:04:25,265 --> 00:04:27,194
Forget it...!

78
00:04:27,620 --> 00:04:29,729
Just do one thing for me.

79
00:04:31,680 --> 00:04:34,290
Do it with me!

80
00:04:40,721 --> 00:04:42,055
Do what...?

81
00:04:42,056 --> 00:04:44,652
Wh-wh-what exactly?

82
00:04:44,653 --> 00:04:46,429
An interview... an interview!

83
00:04:46,430 --> 00:04:49,121
He stutters when he's nervous...

84
00:04:49,122 --> 00:04:50,430
Thirty minutes is all I need!

85
00:04:50,431 --> 00:04:52,792
Just a thirty-minute interview.

86
00:04:56,400 --> 00:05:01,267
Tomorrow at 4 PM, at my place.

87
00:05:01,268 --> 00:05:03,370
Send him the address.

88
00:05:10,400 --> 00:05:11,757
About what happened earlier.

89
00:05:11,758 --> 00:05:13,779
I wanted to apologize for him...

90
00:05:13,780 --> 00:05:16,369
You didn't do anything wrong.

91
00:05:16,370 --> 00:05:18,699
He's just like that sometimes.

92
00:05:18,700 --> 00:05:22,148
But he has his reasons.

93
00:05:23,070 --> 00:05:24,579
He's lucky.

94
00:05:24,580 --> 00:05:25,440
Huh?

95
00:05:25,441 --> 00:05:28,740
He always has someone on his side.

96
00:05:29,569 --> 00:05:30,460
Hey!

97
00:05:30,461 --> 00:05:31,769
I'm on your side!

98
00:05:31,770 --> 00:05:33,099
I'll always be on your side!

99
00:05:33,100 --> 00:05:36,569
You'd better stay on my side then.

100
00:05:36,570 --> 00:05:37,959
Here's my number.

101
00:05:37,960 --> 00:05:40,112
Text me, and I'll send the address.

102
00:05:40,113 --> 00:05:42,020
Okay, okay.

103
00:05:42,021 --> 00:05:44,044
So...

104
00:05:51,300 --> 00:05:52,270
Taewoo!

105
00:05:52,271 --> 00:05:53,445
Yeah?

106
00:05:53,446 --> 00:05:56,000
He wasn't always like that.

107
00:05:56,001 --> 00:05:57,263
What?

108
00:05:57,264 --> 00:05:59,659
Your brother...

109
00:06:01,294 --> 00:06:04,631
Never mind... see you later.

110
00:06:18,730 --> 00:06:20,709
Are you an angel?

111
00:06:20,710 --> 00:06:21,600
Yeah, pretty much.

112
00:06:21,601 --> 00:06:24,169
Then can I have the other popsicle too?

113
00:06:24,170 --> 00:06:25,359
Don't be greedy.

114
00:06:25,360 --> 00:06:26,679
And here I thought you were an angel.

115
00:06:26,680 --> 00:06:29,209
You're the type who'd
steal an angel's underwear.

116
00:06:33,590 --> 00:06:36,769
That text scared the life out of me.

117
00:06:36,770 --> 00:06:38,459
When they said they'd call a lawyer,

118
00:06:38,460 --> 00:06:40,449
I got nervous too.

119
00:06:40,450 --> 00:06:41,680
Is that why you said I was a lawyer?

120
00:06:41,681 --> 00:06:43,489
Yeah.

121
00:06:43,490 --> 00:06:45,039
That's fraud, you know.

122
00:06:45,040 --> 00:06:47,049
Whatever.

123
00:06:47,050 --> 00:06:49,180
It worked out in the end, anyway.

124
00:06:51,690 --> 00:06:54,809
So why is it so awkward
between you and your brother?

125
00:06:54,810 --> 00:06:57,339
Didn't you just see why?

126
00:06:57,340 --> 00:06:59,639
Yeah, I guess...

127
00:07:01,490 --> 00:07:03,699
You know my parents are divorced, right?

128
00:07:03,700 --> 00:07:05,519
Yeah, I know.

129
00:07:05,520 --> 00:07:07,289
Did you know my dad went to prison?

130
00:07:07,290 --> 00:07:09,549
I didn't... wait, what?

131
00:07:09,550 --> 00:07:10,559
Sorry, sorry, sorry.

132
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,249
Did I act too surprised?

133
00:07:12,250 --> 00:07:14,209
A little bit, yeah.

134
00:07:14,210 --> 00:07:16,379
But why?

135
00:07:16,380 --> 00:07:17,822
My brother's the one who reported him.

136
00:07:17,823 --> 00:07:19,519
What?

137
00:07:23,143 --> 00:07:25,712
After the divorce,

138
00:07:26,360 --> 00:07:28,419
my brother blew up as a child star.

139
00:07:28,420 --> 00:07:30,650
My mom was always busy with him.

140
00:07:32,400 --> 00:07:36,579
My dad still came to see me sometimes...

141
00:07:36,580 --> 00:07:38,170
At least I had him.

142
00:07:38,171 --> 00:07:40,610
I didn't feel as lonely...

143
00:07:41,975 --> 00:07:44,499
But maybe he missed my brother too.

144
00:07:44,500 --> 00:07:47,574
He'd just take him away without a word.

145
00:07:49,233 --> 00:07:51,689
Hey... is it okay for me to hear all this?

146
00:07:51,690 --> 00:07:54,841
If it's not you , then who else is going to listen?

147
00:07:56,840 --> 00:08:00,809
My mom and brother reported him.

148
00:08:00,810 --> 00:08:03,249
He ended up in prison.

149
00:08:04,091 --> 00:08:06,191
Truthfully, that's just what my grandma told me.

150
00:08:06,192 --> 00:08:09,262
So I don't know the whole story...

151
00:08:09,610 --> 00:08:12,892
Did it become... better for you?

152
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,050
No.

153
00:08:21,760 --> 00:08:25,232
My mom got even more protective of him.

154
00:08:26,430 --> 00:08:29,240
I just got pushed aside even more.

155
00:08:31,060 --> 00:08:34,280
Honestly, my brother
didn't do anything wrong.

156
00:08:35,170 --> 00:08:37,429
But I feel like he stole
my parents from me.

157
00:08:37,430 --> 00:08:39,066
So I just grew to resent him.

158
00:08:40,313 --> 00:08:41,839
Am I being childish?

159
00:08:41,840 --> 00:08:43,290
No!

160
00:08:43,549 --> 00:08:45,324
Not at all!

161
00:08:48,646 --> 00:08:50,519
You grew up well.

162
00:08:50,520 --> 00:08:53,549
And honestly, you're way
more handsome than your brother.

163
00:08:53,550 --> 00:08:55,680
You're smart, too.

164
00:08:56,510 --> 00:08:58,579
True.

165
00:08:58,580 --> 00:08:59,629
I'm the best, aren't I?

166
00:08:59,630 --> 00:09:00,530
Wait, what?!

167
00:09:00,531 --> 00:09:01,808
Fine, fine.

168
00:09:14,600 --> 00:09:19,500
"Fan Service"
(Episode 2)

169
00:09:21,380 --> 00:09:23,070
Um... hey!

170
00:09:26,180 --> 00:09:29,030
Could I... get an autograph?

171
00:09:33,020 --> 00:09:35,374
My name is Noh Jaeil.

172
00:09:40,966 --> 00:09:42,682
Thank you!

173
00:09:47,828 --> 00:09:50,161
(William)

174
00:09:51,681 --> 00:09:53,681
That prick...

175
00:09:56,126 --> 00:09:58,854
Want to know what his cards meant?

176
00:10:04,104 --> 00:10:11,609
The first card means no romantic feelings.
It's more like friendship or family.

177
00:10:12,210 --> 00:10:20,210
The second is platonic love.
Deeper than friends, but not lovers.

178
00:10:21,610 --> 00:10:27,410
The last one says they'll be like family,
but never a couple.

179
00:10:27,511 --> 00:10:30,600
(What about that extra card?)

180
00:10:31,401 --> 00:10:37,950
That's the one chance I gave him.

181
00:10:38,774 --> 00:10:41,974
Whether he takes it... I don't know.

182
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:43,710
(But why are you talking informally more and more...?)

183
00:10:44,010 --> 00:10:45,170
30,000 won.

184
00:10:45,270 --> 00:10:46,080
(You said 20,000 earlier...)

185
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:47,500
30,000 won...

